{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"547413d4-055a-42f5-a8c9-e01add252d5c","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  .NET 10 Web API                        │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                        │\n│  POST /api/documents/ingest                            │\n│    ├─ MarkdownChunker (split by heading / token limit) │\n│    ├─ EmbeddingService (call OpenAI/Azure OpenAI)      │\n│    └─ VectorStore.Upsert(chunks + embeddings)          │\n│                                                        │\n│  POST /api/qa/ask                                      │\n│    ├─ EmbeddingService (embed the question)            │\n│    ├─ VectorStore.Search(top-K similar chunks)         │\n│    └─ LlmService (generate answer grounded in chunks)  │\n│                                                        │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         │                          │\n         ▼                          ▼\n  ┌──────────────┐        ┌─────────────────┐\n  │ Vector Store │        │  LLM Provider   │\n  │ (in-memory   │        │ (Azure OpenAI / │\n  │  or Qdrant)  │        │  OpenAI API)    │\n  └──────────────┘        └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility |\n|-------|---------------|\n| **MarkdownChunker** | Splits `.md` files on headings (`#`, `##`) with a max token window (~500 tokens). Preserves source file + heading as metadata. |\n| **EmbeddingService** | Wraps `text-embedding-3-small` (or equivalent). Returns `float[]` per chunk. |\n| **VectorStore** | Stores chunks + embeddings. Start with an in-memory `IVectorStore` (cosine similarity); swap to Qdrant/Azure AI Search later. |\n| **LlmService** | Sends a system prompt + retrieved chunks + user question to GPT-4o / equivalent. Returns a grounded answer with source citations. |\n\n---\n\n## Endpoints\n\n1. **`POST /api/documents/ingest`** — reads all `Docs/*.md` files (or an uploaded file), chunks them, embeds, and stores. Returns chunk count.\n2. **`POST /api/qa/ask`** — accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`, retrieves top-K chunks, calls the LLM, returns `{ \"answer\", \"sources\" }`.\n\n---\n\n## Suggested NuGet Packages\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` — unified AI abstraction (embeddings + chat)\n- `Microsoft.SemanticKernel` (optional) — orchestration, memory connectors\n- `Markdig` — markdown parsing for heading-aware chunking\n\n---\n\n## Chunking Strategy\n\n1. Parse markdown into a block AST (Markdig).\n2. Split on H1/H2 boundaries.\n3. If a section exceeds the token limit, further split on paragraphs with overlap (~50 tokens).\n4. Each chunk carries metadata: `{ file, heading, startLine }`.\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions to Confirm\n\n- **Vector store**: start in-memory (simplest) or external (Qdrant/Azure AI Search)?\n- **LLM provider**: Azure OpenAI or openai.com direct?\n- **Auth**: should the endpoints be protected, or is this internal-only for now?\n- **Ingestion trigger**: on-demand endpoint, startup hook, or file-watcher?\n\nLet me know your preferences on those choices, or say **\"implement it\"** and I'll build it with sensible defaults (in-memory store, Azure OpenAI, no auth, on-demand ingestion).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c37482bc-4356-4b91-882f-2a1bd9fd4d53","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the existing project. Let me create a plan for the RAG-based Q&A feature.","outputTokens":1006,"requestId":"A402:87F76:15B8335:184CB8C:69FD33DB"},"id":"36d7c2ce-f128-4c89-8e21-4cc3ba0dce21","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:04.635Z","parentId":"f9c05f2d-9d64-49b4-9bb0-82e09784e4f8"}
